basics about docker


What Docker Solves
Docker packages:
Application+Libraries+Dependencies+Runtime into a single unit called a Container.

Developer Laptop
       ↓
QA Server
       ↓
Production

runs exactly the same.

Virtual Machine vs Container
Virtual Machine
Physical Server
    ↓
Hypervisor
    ↓
VM1 (Guest OS)
VM2 (Guest OS)
VM3 (Guest OS)

Each VM has its own OS.

Heavy.
More RAM.
Slow startup.

Docker Container
Physical Server
      ↓
Host OS
      ↓
Docker Engine
      ↓
Container1
Container2
Container3

Containers share the host OS kernel.

Lightweight.
Fast startup.
Less memory.
Docker container share the OS kernel and provide many benefits such as less cost and faster result.

